{
  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "AI agents could also be used for generating ideas and brainstorming, as far as the initial text is created by the human author (Creamer, 2023).",
    "We consider these guidelines from Amazon crucial for identifying the AI role in writing texts because AI-generated works cannot be protected by copyright (Brittain, 2023).",
    "Despite the versatile opportunities, AI technologies impose their own limitations, such as the lack of transparency and reproduction of already existing biases (Abdul et al., 2018).",
    "Chatbot also lacks an understanding of the semantic contents of narrative discourse, as well as the psychological faculties and communicative practices that constitute fiction as a practice (Ghajargar et al., 2022, p. 232).",
    "Oloff C. Biermann et al. (2022) elicited three sets of primary barriers to the adoption of human-AI cowriting: 1) dominance of emotional values over AI-generated writing productivity; 2) distrust in AI when challenging sub-tasks such as creating characters and dialogue; and 3) expectation that the AI generating strategies will mismatch the writer's initial intention."
  ],
